3%-28% of women suffer from partial PPPTSD.

 Neuro Linguistic Programming (NLP) is a "one-on-one" intervention method, connecting Neurological processes (N), Linguistic (L) and learned behaviors (P), in order to allow conceptual/perceptual, mental and behavioral changes.

 Even though NLP is used since the 1970's and field testimonies report its effectiveness, there are only few studies regarding its effectiveness in the field of PTSD.

 "Group intervention", which combines both CBT tools and dynamic group therapy, is part of the common treatment usually implemented at Maccabi Healthcare Services in the event of PTSD.

 This study's main objective is to examine the effectiveness of the NLP PTSD protocol in comparison to the common intervention protocol used at Maccabi Healthcare Services in Israel (Treatment as usual).

 The study population will include 60 women, up to one year after birth, with PPPTSD, out of which 30 will be treated in 12 sessions implementing Maccabi Healthcare Services common group protocol and 30 will be treated in 5 individual sessions implementing the NLP PTSD protocol.

